HEADWORD: Fan-nerved
<hw>Fan"-nerved`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Bot. &
Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the nerves or veins arranged in a radiating
manner; -- said of certain leaves, and of the wings of some
insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

